            . I am shopman to Mr. 
               <persName id="t18240603-245-person2089">
                  Thomas 
                  Rees
               <interp inst="t18240603-245-person2089" type="surname" value="Rees"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-245-person2089" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18240603-245-person2089" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , <rs id="t18240603-245-viclabel1273" type="occupation">linendraper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240603-245-victim2087 t18240603-245-viclabel1273"></join>, <placeName id="t18240603-245-crimeloc1274">Shoreditch</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18240603-245-crimeloc1274" type="placeName" value="Shoreditch"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18240603-245-crimeloc1274" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18240603-245-off1271 t18240603-245-crimeloc1274"></join>. The prisoner came to our shop on Saturday evening last, about eight o'clock, and asked to look at some ribbons - I showed her some - she said she wanted narrow white ribbon - I placed the drawer on the counter, and she ordered one yard and a half of one, and two yards of another, to be cut off - she had not asked any price, which made me suspect she had taken some - there was another person in the shop, at a distance - I turned my head, and when I looked round I missed one of the ribbons, and charged her with it - she immediately pulled a piece from her pocket - I think I had said,</p>
               <p>"You have got a piece of ribbon in your pocket;" she had not gone from the shop - I then said,</p>
               <p>"How many more have you got;" she was putting her hand again to her pocket, and I got over the counter and took her to the end of the shop - she said she had laid two half-crowns on the counter - it is very unusual for women to come into a shop and take ribbons without asking the price - no other person served her - I saw her come in; and as soon as I took her to the end of the shop, she said she had put two half-crowns on the counter, which I had not seen before - I went and found one on the counter, and one in the drawer.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-245-person2090">
                  JOSHUA 
                  ARMSTRONG
               <interp inst="t18240603-245-person2090" type="surname" value="ARMSTRONG"></interp>
