             - these two pieces of ribbon were taken from the pocket of the prisoner.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I went to the shop to buy one yard and a half of ribbon at 3 1/2 d. per yard, and two yards at 5 d. - I asked for some other - he laid hold of me, and shook my hand, and said I was going to steal the ribbon - one gentleman came in with one half-crown, and said it does not belong to her, it belongs to somebody else - I said I had given two half-crowns, and the officer sent him to look for the other, which he found.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18240603-245-person2093">
